4. A man purchased a table and a chair for Rs.2000. He sold the table at a profit of 20% and the chair at a profit of 40%. In this way, his total profit was 25%. Find the cost price (in Rs.) of the table.


You have max 2 attempts to score in this question.
Attempts left:
1/2
Options
This problem has only one correct answer
1500
900
800
1000
Hurray! Correct Answer
Solution Description


When we plot the 20% and 40% profit in the number line, the difference will be 20.

But analysing the weighted average situation, the average of both the profits will be 25%.

Therefore, the ratio of the two groups (Table and Chair) will be  15 : 5

The total sum of the ratio is 20, but according to the question, it will be 2000, which is 100 times of 20.

Therefore, the cost price of the table will also be 15 * 100 times = 1500

Hence, the correct option will be option(a).


